To create a proper .gitignore file for an ASP.NET Core project, you can use the following template. This ensures that unnecessary files (e.g., build artifacts, user-specific settings, and temporary files) are excluded from version control:
# Build results
bin/
obj/

# User-specific files
*.user
*.userosscache
*.suo
*.userprefs

# Logs
*.log
logs/

# Visual Studio specific
.vscode/
.vs/
*.ncrunchsolution
*.ncrunchproject
*.sln.docstates

# Dependency directories
node_modules/
bower_components/

# Generated files
*.dll
*.exe
*.pdb
*.cache
*.ilk
*.idb
*.lib
*.log
*.obj
*.o
*.os
*.so
*.swp
*.tmp
*.tmp.*
*.csproj.user
*.dbmdl
*.jfm
*.pfx
*.publishsettings

# ASP.NET Core specific
appsettings*.json
appsettings*.Development.json
appsettings*.Production.json

# Rider IDE specific
.idea/
*.sln.iml

# Other
*.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
